\n                    \n\n                    \n                      \n                        This document provides a comprehensive explanation of the Markdown footnote syntax supported by the markdown-it-footnote plugin. It covers the different types of footnotes, their syntax rules, and formatting requirements.\n                      \n                    \n\n                    \n                  \n                \n              \n            \n              \n                \n                   \n                    \n                      \n                        Adding Footnotes and Notes to Markdown Using markdown-it-footnote\n                      \n\n                    \n\n                    \n                      \n                        \n                          \n                            \n                              \n                            \n                          \n                          \n                            debugtips.com/adding-footnotes-and-notes-to-markdown-using-markdown-it-footnote\n                          \n                          \n                        \n                      \n                    \n\n                    \n                      \n                        While Markdown allows various HTML tags to be used, this article is about how to use footnotes and notes. We&#x27;ll use the Node.js package library markdown-it-footnote to enable footnotes and notes in Markdown.\n                      \n                    \n\n                    \n                  \n                \n              \n            \n              \n                \n                   \n                    \n                      \n                        markdown-it-footnote - npm\n                      \n\n                    \n\n                    \n                      \n                        \n                          \n                            \n                              \n                           