         \n                      \n                        \n                          \n                            \n                              \n                            \n                          \n                          \n                            www.xjavascript.com/blog/markdown-typescript/\n                          \n                          \n                            &nbsp; &nbsp; 2025-10-19T00:00:00.0000000\n                          \n                        \n                      \n                    \n\n                    \n                      \n                        Markdown is a lightweight markup language that allows users to write formatted text using plain-text syntax. It has become extremely popular due to its simplicity and widespread use in documentation, blogging, and README files. TypeScript, on the other hand, is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. Combining Markdown with TypeScript can bring new capabilities to ...\n                      \n                    \n\n                    \n                  \n                \n              \n            \n\n            \n              \n              \n                \n                  \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n\n                    \n                    \n                    \n                      \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                  \n                \n              \n            \n\n            \n              Feedback","title":"https://duckduckgo.com/html/?q=markdown+footnote+plugin+typescript (text/html; charset=UTF-8)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772754812118,"end":1772754813152}}}}
